{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Embedding vector dimensionality matches the vector index dimension for a given query.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The real failure boundary is the contract between the live embedding provider output shape and the live index schema. A mock embedding client can hide provider/model-version dimension drift; catching that requires a real model/API call and real index interaction.","test_description":"Call the real embedding endpoint configured for production model, then upsert/query against a test index with the production dimension setting and assert the returned vector length exactly equals index dimension; fail on mismatch.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.55,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Similarity search results are ordered by descending cosine similarity.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is primarily a module-boundary/data-contract issue between retrieval code and vector DB scoring/order semantics. It does not require external internet services if run against a local test vector store with known vectors.","test_description":"Seed a local test vector DB with fixed vectors and run the similarity query path used by the API; assert returned scores are monotonically non-increasing and IDs match expected cosine order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"LLM re-ranking changes at least some ordering for nuanced-intent queries.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real LLM judgment over nuance, which is non-deterministic and quality-dependent. Mocked or rule-based rerankers can pass while missing real model behavior.","test_description":"Run the reranking step with a real LLM on a curated nuanced query set where lexical similarity alone is insufficient; across repeated trials, assert at least one top-K position changes from raw similarity ranking in a minimum fraction of cases.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"No-close-match queries return an empty set, not low-relevance noise.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure usually appears at the handoff between retrieval scores and relevance-threshold filtering logic. This can be caught with real module wiring and a local vector DB; no real external model quality judgment is required.","test_description":"Populate a local index with domain-specific vectors, issue out-of-domain queries through the API retrieval/filter path, and assert the final result set is empty when all similarities are below configured threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Median end-to-end query latency (ingest -> embedding -> retrieval -> rerank -> response) is below 2 seconds.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The risk is in real runtime behavior across subprocess/network/external API boundaries. Mocking these dependencies hides true latency distribution, so real service calls are needed.","test_description":"Execute a representative load run against the deployed API path using real embedding and reranking services, collect end-to-end latency for sufficient sample size, and assert p50 < 2000 ms.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.05}}]}
